snippet.textDisplay: Here's the thing guys, I have seen a lot of people shut down fire emblem because they think it isn't mainstream, or because the series isn't as big as pokemon or mario. Well I'm here to shut down that argument. Fire emblem IS mainstream for Nintendo now: Whether you like it or not. It is their 17th game, and has a life span of 31 years now. It has out lived a lot of other nintendo ip's, such as F-zero, earthbound, and even metroid (don't flame me with replies, I know Metroid Prime 4 is coming it's just they haven't made a new one original metroid game in a while). Just because you haven't played Fire Emblem, doesn't mean it isn't popular. Since Awakening (excluding Fire emblem Echoes), each game has sold ridiculously well, each installment coming close to or exceeding the sales of the last. It only makes sense that they would capitalize on Three Houses' success. Byleth is different than all the other fire emblem characters, Sakuri thoroughly made sure of that (even making a joke of it in the cutscene). Even if Byleth isn't your cup of tea, you don't HAVE to buy them, let other people enjoy them. Just because you don't like them, doesn't mean other's can't, and it definitely doesn't take away any of the beauty that is Smash Brothers Ultimate. We still have 6 other characters coming, and possibly more (who knows!). But please don't insult Sakuri's choices, or flame him on twitter for something he CLEARLY had a ton of fun making.  He has put SO MUCH WORK into this game, and has probably included the most fan opinion in the game. With characters that won't profit nintendo in the slightest because the game(s) they are from are no longer relevant, like K rool, Ridely, Banjo Kazooie. The major reason characters like that are included are for YOU, the fans. Even the fighter's pass includes Joker, who isn't even on any nintendo console and doesn't boost their popularity in any way, was included, along with characters from other franchises new to Smash, So including one out of (at the time of this commnet) 11 characters being a nintendo character from a franchise already existing within the game, is really no big deal whatsoever, stop making it one.

snippet.textDisplay:
Fire Emblem is a fantasy tactical role-playing game franchise developed by Intelligent Systems and published by Nintendo. First produced and published for the Family Computer (Famicom), the series consists of sixteen main games and three spin-offs. Described by its creators as a "role-playing game simulation, the gameplay revolves around tactical movement of characters across grid-based environments, while incorporating a story and characters similar to traditional role-playing video games.

A noted aspect of gameplay is the permanent death of characters in battle, removing them from the rest of the game should they be defeated. In the newer titles, from Fire Emblem: New Mystery of the Emblem onwards, players get the choice between Classic mode, where characters permanently die, or Casual mode, where fallen characters revive for the next battle. The series title refers to the "Fire Emblem", usually portrayed as a royal weapon or shield that represents the power of war and dragons, a recurring element in the series. Development of the first game began as a dōjin project by Shouzou Kaga and three other developers. Its success prompted the development of further titles in the series. Shouzou Kaga headed development of each entry until the release of Thracia 776, when he left Intelligent Systems and founded his own game studio to develop Tear Ring Saga.

Advance Wars, the 2001 turn-based tactics game, had previously released before Super Smash Bros. Melee two months prior, which was such a success that Designer Kentaro Nishimura stated “Advance Wars’ success shifted Nintendo’s attitude over western tastes.” Additionally, he goes to say that the Fire Emblem series would have never crossed the seas to the west had Advance Wars not make a prominent impact.

No games in the series were released outside of Japan until two characters, Marth and Roy, were included as playable characters in the 2001 fighting game Super Smash Bros. Melee. Their popularity eventually convinced Nintendo to release the next game, The Blazing Blade, in Western regions under the title Fire Emblem in 2003. Many games in the series have sold well, despite a decline during the 2000s which resulted in the series' near-cancellation. Individual entries have generally been praised, and the series as a whole has been lauded for its gameplay, and it is cited as a seminal series in the tactical role-playing genre. Characters from multiple games have also been included in crossovers with other franchises.

snippet.textDisplay:
I think people calling the others "toxic" because some of them pushed the dislike button have misanderstand something. There's a lot of reasons that convinced some users to do that... and good reasons depending of the point of view. In my case, i dislike this video because i want to be aware when my money goes into Nintendo's commercial stuff.

I explain :
(Note: i'm french so i'm sorry in advance if my english is not perfect)

First, i respect the work of Sakurai and his team and that's why i've bought the game at launch. I didn't do the same thing with the DLC #1 because we didn't know the name of the fighters and because i'm thinking 25$ for five characters plus stages was too expensive but, after seeing Joker, Hero and Banjo Kazooie, i was conviced that the content from this DLC had an incredible potential so i've use my credit card without any regrets... until now.

To be clear, if i'm very happy to see Hero and Banjo Kazooie in this game, i don't feel the same thing with Joker and Terry Bogard because i don't looking for them... however! I'm not complaining about this characters because they're clever choices when we thinking at "celebration of gaming". Also, like everyone, i'm wanting a special character but i'm not going to spam Sakurai's Twitter account for that and i'm fine with the actual character roster.

So... what's the problem with Byleth?

- He does not deserve to be in SSB?
> Why not?

- It's because he's a sword fighter?
> No, plus he can use all kinds of weapons.

- He's uncool?
> No, he looks cool like his gameplay.

- He's part of the FE crew?
> Yes, i think this fact is a part of the problem but i can overcome this.

- So? Why i've pushing the dislike button then?
> Because he's clearly here for selling FE games first.

Seriously, look at this video regardless of the good mood of Sakurai. What's FE? What's FE:Three Houses? And the trailer for the DLC of the game at the end of the presentation? Huh... we've spend money for special guest characters like the previous ones or for helping Nintendo to expand the FE franchise? Moreover, Byleth was the last entry from the DLC #1 and after Joker & Co, everybody (absolutely everybody) who bought this pack believe that's the final character was truly unique like the others. It's clearly not the case and that's why a lot of people were disapointed.

It's understandable: Joker introduced Atlus and one of the coolest RPG from this era, Hero introduced the biggest RPG series created in Japan, Banjo Kazooie it's like Rare finally returned at home, Terry Bogard introduced one of the greatest arcade manufacturer of all time and Byleth... Byleth is here for selling games and DLC when his franchise is perfectly represented with seven characters... yeah, it make sens... business sens.

Do not mistake yourself, i'm not looking to be disrespectful towards Sakurai when i've say that. I like the guy, i like the game but when something goes wrong i have to say it. For me, it's like i'm starting writing a book with the idea of making peoples happy and then after reading it, 35% of the readers want to kill themselves because i've decided to put some dark subliminal messages in the final chapter. "But why my hard work stimulate the anger of their families? Be gratefull because there's a sequel in the way, you know?" lol No, sorry, it's just a bad move and there's no wickedness in my words.

Anyway, i suspect Nintendo for intentionnaly put Byleth at the end because it was impossible they weren't aware about the fact that this one will be controversial. It's now obvious to say this character was the worst choice for creating hype around the fighters pass and that's why i think it's good for them to cloture the DLC #1 with Byleth (since most of the players bought this pack) and starting promote DLC #2 with a major character such as Geno or someone "everybody" want.

For now, i'm pretty confident for the next ones regardless on who they are, even if this troll make me fear another Pokemon for promoting Sword & Shield DLC although there's aleready Incineroar in this game. It would be the worst so i hope i'm wrong.

Thank you for reading.
